commit.title: [gitlab] Add bleeding-edge flambda build.
commit.message:
[gitlab] Add bleeding-edge flambda build.

I also introduced a bit more systematic job naming.

This is as we are getting close to being able to remove quite a few
builds from Travis.

Note the extra quote rule for the flambda parameters, but unless we
can assign arrays to Gitlab variables there is not a good way to do
this I'm afraid.
